y]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-Lyndon B Johnson.png|[[Lyndon B. Johnson]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-Richard Nixon.png|[[Richard Nixon]]\nFile:Galup Poll-Approval Rating-Gerald Ford.png|[[Gerald Ford]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-Jimmy Carter.png|[[Jimmy Carter]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-Ronald Reagan.png|[[Ronald Reagan]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-George H W Bush.png|[[George H. W. Bush]]\nFile:Galup Poll-Approval Rating-Bill Clinton.png|[[Bill Clinton]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-George W Bush.png|[[George W. Bush]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-Barack Obama.svg|[[Barack Obama]]\nFile:Gallup Poll-Approval Rating-Donald Trump.svg|[[Donald Trump]]\n</gallery>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Historical rankings of Presidents of the United States]]\n* [[Opinion polling on the Donald Trump administration]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://presidential.roper.center/ \"Historical Presidential Job Performance Ratings\"]. Roper Center.\n* [https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/trump-approval-ratings/ \"Trump approval ratings\"]. FiveThirtyEight.\n* [http://www.data360.org/graph_group.aspx?Graph_Group_Id=292 \"Midterm Presidential Approval Ratings\"]. Data360.\n* [http://www.presidentpollsusa.com \"President Job Approval Ratings\"]. PresidentPollsUSA.\n* [https://online.wsj.com/public/resources/documents/info-presapp0605-31.html \"Historical Presidential Approval Ratings 1945\u20132009\"]. ''The Wall Street Journal''.\n* [http://www.congressratings.com/29/obama-barack-d-il/ \"President Obama's Ongoing Job Approval\"]. (CongressRatings)\n\n{{Lists of US Presidents and Vice Presidents}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:United States Presidential Approval Rating}}\n[[Category:Opinion polling in the United States|presidential approval rating]]\n[[Category:United States presidential history|presidential approval rating]]\n[[Category:Historical rankings of public figures]]\n[[Category:Rating]]\n", "text_old": "{{use mdy dates|date=April 2012}}\nIn the '''United States, presidential job approval ratings''' were introduced by [[George Gallup]] in the late 1930s (estimated to be 1937) to gauge public support for the [[president of the United States]] during their term. An approval rating is a percentage determined by a polling which indicates the percentage of respondents to an opinion poll who approve of a particular person or program. Typically, an approval rating is given to a [[politician]] based on responses to a poll in which a sample of people are asked whether they approve or disapprove of that particular political figure. A question might ask: \n<br />\n:Do you approve or disapprove of the way Donald Trump is handling his job as president?<ref name=\"Donald Trump Gallup Polling Data\" />\n\nLike most surveys that predict opinions, individual poll results may be inaccurate. Many unscientific approval rating systems exist that show inaccurate statistics. Examples that self select, such as online questions are of this type. However, the aggregate approval rating is generally accepted by statisticians, as a statistically valid indicator of the comparative changes in the popular United States mood regarding a president. \n\nPresident Donald Trump in 2018 had a job approval of approximately 75 to 90 percent among Republicans and 5 to 10 percent among Democrats.<ref name=\"Donald Trump Gallup Polling Data\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gallup.com/poll/203198/presidential-approval-ratings-donald-trump.aspx|title=Presidential Approval Ratings \u2013 Donald Trump|work=Gallup|accessdate=February 13, 2017}} </ref> Gallup polling has found that, as of 2019, 47% of Americans are either \"Democrats or Democratic leaners\" while 42% are either \"Republicans or Republican leaners\".<ref>{{cite web|title=U.S. Party Preferences Steady During Trump Era|url=https://news.gallup.com/poll/274694/party-preferences-steady-during-trump-era.aspx|work=[[Gallup (company)|Gallup]]|author=Jeffrey M. Jones|accessdate=23 January 2020|date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== President Donald Trump ==\n{{main article|Opinion polling on the Donald Trump administration}}\n'''Most recent polls for President Donald J. Trump'''<ref name=PROTRUMP>{{cite web|url=http://www.pollingreport.com/djt_job.htm|title=President Trump: Job Ratings|work=PollingReport.com|accessdate=August 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realclearpolitics.com/epolls/other/president_trump_job_approval-6179.html|title=President Trump Job Approval|work=RealClearPolitics|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Comparing\">{{cite web|title=How (un)popular is Donald Trump?|url=https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/trump-approval-ratings/|website=fivethirtyeight.com|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Polling group\n!Date \n!Approval \n!Disapproval \n!Unsure\n!Net +/-\n!Sample size<ref name=\"Comparing\"/>\n!Population<ref name=\"Comparing\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.realclearpolitics.com/epolls/other/president_trump_job_approval-6179.html|title=President Trump Job Approval|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Rasmussen Reports]]<ref name=\"RASTRUMP\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rasmussenreports.com/public_content/politics/trump_administration/trump_approval_index_history|title=Trump Approval Index History|accessdate=November 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|March 31\u2013April 2, 2020\n|44%\n|53%\n|3%\n| -9%\n|{{sort|1500|\u22481,500}}\n|Likely voters\n|-\n|[[Ipsos]]/[[Reuters]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://polling.reuters.com/#poll/CP3_2/|title=Trump approval at reuters.com|accessdate=June 17, 2017}}</ref>\n|March 30\u201331, 2020\n|44%\n|51%\n|5%\n| -7%\n|1,114\n|All adults\n|-\n|[[Kaiser Family Foundation]]{{efn|name=ssrs}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kff.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Kaiser-Health-Tracking-Poll_Early-April_Full-Topline_FINAL.pdf|title=KFF Health Tracking Poll 